data.chText: 专指的，特指的（与泛指相对）
data.enText: used to emphasize that you are referring to one individual person, thing or type of thing and not others

data.chText: 我想让你见一个病人。
data.enText: There is one particular patient I'd like you to see.

data.chText: 他有特别喜爱的哪一类书籍吗？
data.enText: Is there a particular type of book he enjoys?

data.chText: 不寻常的；格外的；特别的
data.enText: greater than usual; special

data.chText: 我们必须特别注意这一点。
data.enText: We must pay particular attention to this point.

data.chText: 这些文件让人尤其感兴趣。
data.enText: These documents are of particular interest.

data.chText: 讲究；挑剔
data.enText: very definite about what you like and careful about what you choose

data.chText: 她对衣着特别挑剔。
data.enText: She's very particular about her clothes.
in particular

data.chText: 尤其；特别；格外
data.enText: especially or particularly

data.chText: 他特别喜爱科幻小说。
data.enText: He loves science fiction in particular.

data.chText: 特殊的；专门的；具体的
data.enText: special or specific

data.chText: 彼得躺在沙发上，无所事事。
data.enText: Peter was lying on the sofa doing nothing in particular .

data.chText: 晚饭你有具体想吃的吗？
data.enText: Is there anything in particular you'd like for dinner?

data.chText: 她的问题并没有针对任何个人。
data.enText: She directed the question at no one in particular .

data.chText: （正式记下的）细节，详情
data.enText: a fact or detail especially one that is officially written down

data.chText: 这名警察记下了窃案发生的详细情况。
data.enText: The police officer took down all the particulars of the burglary.

data.chText: 护士向我询问了我的个人资料。
data.enText: The nurse asked me for my particulars (= personal details such as your name, address, etc.).

data.chText: 新合同与旧合同的各项细节将完全相同。
data.enText: The new contract will be the same in every particular as the old one.

data.chText: 详细资料；详细介绍材料
data.enText: written information and details about a property, business, job, etc.

data.chText: 申请表格及其他详细资料可向人事部索取。
data.enText: Application forms and further particulars are available from the Personnel Office.

simple_means.memory_skill: part 部分；分开 + icular 有…性质的 → 属于自己的部分 → 各自的

means: 专指的，特指的(与泛指相对)

ex.chText: 酒吧里有一块专门用于聊天的地方。
ex.enText: There is a special place in the bar for chatting.

ex.chText: 她用特殊的方法做蛋挞。
ex.enText: She has a special recipe for egg tart.

ex.chText: 你们结婚15周年纪念有什么特别活动吗？
ex.enText: Are you doing anything special for your 15th wedding anniversary?

ex.chText: 处理此事我们需要你的特殊才能。
ex.enText: We need your special talents for handling this matter.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指事物在质量、特性、用途等方面不同于一般的，常含更重要或更好之意。

ex.chText: 我妹妹对蘑菇有着特殊的偏好。
ex.enText: My sister has an especial fondness for mushrooms.

ex.chText: 这是一件特别重要的事情。
ex.enText: This is a matter of especial importance.
He has an especial dislike for jazz music.

synonyms.bx: 和 special 基本同义，但更强调在程度上超出一般的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 你有什么特别的计划吗？
ex.enText: Do you have anything particular planned?
You should pay particular attention to grammar.

ex.chText: 她特别关心那名残疾儿童。
ex.enText: She showed particular concern for the disabled child.

synonyms.bx: 强调个性或特殊性，即侧重于个别的、特别的、不同于一般的情况、特点等。

ex.chText: 这幅画有一种独特的风格。
ex.enText: The picture has a specific style.

ex.chText: 这钱将用于某种特定用途。
ex.enText: The money is to be used for a specific purpose.

ex.chText: 他要一份对该问题的专门分析。
ex.enText: He wants a specific kind of analysis of the problem.

synonyms.bx: 指某一事物具有特定属性、风格等的，只作定语。

tr: a fact about some part (as opposed to general)
example: he always reasons from the particular to the general

tr: (logic) a proposition that asserts something about some (but not all) members of a class
a small part that can be considered separately from the whole
example: it was perfect in all details
very particular about how her food was prepared
she gets special (or particular) satisfaction from her volunteer work

value.def: You use particular to emphasize that you are talking about one thing or one kind of thing rather than other similar ones.

example.ex: I remembered a particular story about a postman who was a murderer...
example.tran: 我记得有个故事，讲的是一个邮递员杀人的事情。

example.ex: I have to know exactly why it is I'm doing a particular job.
example.tran: 我必须明确知道我为什么要做特定的一项工作。

example.ex: ...if there are particular things you're interested in.
example.tran: 如果有你感兴趣的东西

value.def: If a person or thing has a particular quality or possession, it is distinct and belongs only to them.

example.ex: I have a particular responsibility to ensure I make the right decision...
example.tran: 我肩负特殊责任，必须确保自己作出的决定是正确的。

example.ex: Fatigue is a particular problem for women.
example.tran: 疲劳是女性特有的问题。

value.def: You can use particular to emphasize that something is greater or more intense than usual.

example.ex: Particular emphasis will be placed on oral language training.
example.tran: 将会特别强调口语训练。

value.def: If you say that someone is particular, you mean that they choose things and do things very carefully, and are not easily satisfied.

example.ex: Ted was very particular about the colors he used.
example.tran: 特德在用色上非常讲究。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>about</l> n

value.def: You use in particular to indicate that what you are saying applies especially to one thing or person.

example.ex: The situation in Ethiopia in particular is worrying...
example.tran: 埃塞俄比亚的局势尤其令人担忧。

example.ex: Why should he notice her car in particular?...
example.tran: 他为什么会特别注意到她的车？

example.ex: In particular I admire Gary Lineker.
example.tran: 我特别崇拜加里·莱因克尔。

value.def: You use nothing in particular or nobody in particular to mean nothing or nobody important or special.

example.ex: I went along thinking of nothing in particular only looking at things around me...
example.tran: 我一路走着，没想什么特别的事，只是四下张望着。

example.ex: Drew made some remarks to nobody in particular and said goodbye.
example.tran: 德鲁说了一些不针对任何人的话就告辞了。

value.tran: 没什么重要（或特别）的事物（或人）
